# Fish user messages (echo vs printf)

- Send errors, usage text, and warnings to **stderr** (`>&2`).
- Keep user-facing strings in **English**.

## Which command to use

| Situation | Use |
| --- | --- |
| Fixed one-line message | `echo "…" >&2` |
| Message with `$variables` via format placeholders (`%s`, etc.) | `printf "… %s\n" $var >&2` |
| Snippets meant to match POSIX shells | `printf` (include `\n` in the format string) |

## Do not

- Do not require `printf` for every literal line when `echo` is enough.
- Do not use `echo` for formatted multi-value messages—use `printf` instead.
- Do not omit `>&2` on errors and usage output.

## Examples

```fish
echo "fnm: command not found" >&2
printf "fnm: failed to uninstall %s\n" $v >&2
```

